Note: 
 => Helm is a package manager for Kubernetes that configures and deploys applications and services on a Kubernetes cluster.
 => It uses Helm charts to simplify the development and deployment process.
 => Most Kubernetes deployments require multiple YAML files to configure the necessary resources. Helm charts package all the deployment information into a single chart to simplify the deployment.
 => In short, helm reduce the installation time, upgradation time, deletation time in k8s to make easiler life of end-user.
 => its a third party utility, it is not native product of k8s.

 Helm : it is a kubernetes manifests package manager. like yum in linux which install depelopment automatically

 Helm repo  : It just a folder which contain helm chart.
 	1) Internet based
 	2) Infra based

 repository : it is collections of helm chart.


 Helm chart : Its is a collections of required  manifests to deploy applications.
    charts are two types
    1) Community Based
    2) Custom







